The paper deals with dialog state tracking, which is a subfield of natural language processing and human-computer interaction. The proposed method uses machine reading and memory networks, which are common techniques in the areas of computational linguistics, artificial intelligence, and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves neural networks, which are a popular tool in the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with dialog systems, which are relevant to the sub-category of cs.SD (Software Engineering). Finally, the paper proposes to extend the dataset with specific reasoning capabilities, which is relevant to the sub-category of cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
